1
00:02:52,800 --> 00:02:54,320
- Samut!
- No!

2
00:02:54,880 --> 00:02:56,720
If you're going to shoot Wayu,
shoot me first.

3
00:02:56,800 --> 00:02:59,200
- Fahsai?
- I love him.

4
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:02,640
<i>But there's something else I want to know.</i>

5
00:03:02,720 --> 00:03:04,400
What do you mean?

6
00:03:04,480 --> 00:03:07,240
It's about what you said,
that you love Wayu.

7
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:09,560
What you said, was it true?

8
00:03:10,240 --> 00:03:12,080
- Is it?
- It's so cold my head hurts.

9
00:03:16,920 --> 00:03:18,760
<i>For me to clarify the facts</i>

10
00:03:19,600 --> 00:03:22,000
<i>about what happened that day,</i>
<i>so everyone will know the truth.</i>

11
00:03:22,080 --> 00:03:25,920
Mr. Dharn, is the man
in the clip really you?

12
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:29,040
Do you feel sorry for Mr. Dharn?
Are you disappointed?

13
00:03:30,520 --> 00:03:31,840
Or heartbroken?

14
00:03:41,320 --> 00:03:42,680
Gosh.

15
00:04:05,160 --> 00:04:06,440
You asked for it.

16
00:04:17,040 --> 00:04:21,519
Ms. Fahsai, don't delete it.

17
00:04:23,560 --> 00:04:25,560
I'm so sad.

18
00:04:26,320 --> 00:04:28,200
I'm so sad.

19
00:05:09,560 --> 00:05:10,520
Hey.

20
00:05:12,840 --> 00:05:15,280
How long are you going to ignore me?

21
00:05:19,400 --> 00:05:20,440
I'm tired.

22
00:05:21,400 --> 00:05:23,840
I punched a sandbag for hours.

23
00:05:23,920 --> 00:05:25,640
Where would I get the energy to talk?

24
00:05:30,840 --> 00:05:32,080
Are you shy around me?

25
00:05:36,360 --> 00:05:38,000
Hey…

26
00:05:38,080 --> 00:05:41,000
Even if it wasn't intentional, I liked it.

27
00:05:45,440 --> 00:05:46,960
Can you "not intend" it more often?

28
00:05:49,760 --> 00:05:52,160
What are you saying?

29
00:05:52,240 --> 00:05:53,320
You still have energy left.

30
00:05:54,400 --> 00:05:55,360
You want another one?

31
00:05:56,760 --> 00:05:57,880
Fahsai.

32
00:06:07,360 --> 00:06:08,440
Go upstairs first.

33
00:06:21,640 --> 00:06:23,480
Tell Black Doc

34
00:06:24,600 --> 00:06:26,200
I've paid my debt.

35
00:06:31,680 --> 00:06:34,160
Tell them to stay
the hell out of my business.

36
00:06:37,480 --> 00:06:40,160
Black Doc? Who is that?

37
00:07:07,120 --> 00:07:07,960
Damn it.

38
00:07:08,040 --> 00:07:10,080
Thought people would finally see
how rotten he is,

39
00:07:10,160 --> 00:07:12,160
even just a little.

40
00:07:22,680 --> 00:07:25,880
He dumped everything on Mr. Dharn instead.
It's all over the place now.

41
00:07:25,960 --> 00:07:29,000
That guy got beaten up for free,

42
00:07:29,080 --> 00:07:31,480
then exposed for free too.

43
00:07:31,560 --> 00:07:34,920
If someone's really clean,
no one can expose them.

44
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:37,160
She just likes handsome guys.

45
00:07:37,240 --> 00:07:40,880
Handsome equals innocent,
even if they're trash.

46
00:07:40,960 --> 00:07:44,160
They're all trash. But what really gets me

47
00:07:44,760 --> 00:07:46,480
is that someone worse, like Samut,

48
00:07:46,560 --> 00:07:49,320
exposed someone slightly less bad
and still won.

49
00:07:50,800 --> 00:07:53,600
Mr. Dharn said he didn't force the woman.

50
00:07:53,680 --> 00:07:54,920
But who's going to believe that?

51
00:07:55,000 --> 00:07:56,680
Exactly. No one cares about it anymore.

52
00:07:57,920 --> 00:08:01,040
Once the clip is everywhere, it's over.

53
00:08:01,120 --> 00:08:04,920
Even if people have doubts,
they won't find the victim.

54
00:08:06,320 --> 00:08:07,400
Latest check,

55
00:08:08,400 --> 00:08:09,720
she's already left the country.

56
00:08:12,800 --> 00:08:14,680
Samut's slick.

57
00:08:15,800 --> 00:08:17,120
He turned the whole game around.

58
00:08:22,200 --> 00:08:25,920
Have you ever heard what God said?
To love your neighbor?

59
00:08:27,320 --> 00:08:31,440
For his birthday this year,
I've got a big gift of love for him.

60
00:09:03,760 --> 00:09:07,000
Thank you, thank you.
Please enjoy yourselves.

61
00:09:07,080 --> 00:09:09,320
Please go ahead. Thank you.

62
00:09:11,200 --> 00:09:13,960
‪Congratulations, Mr. Mahasamut.
‪Happy Birthday!

63
00:09:14,520 --> 00:09:16,720
- Thank you.
- You've done well.

64
00:09:16,800 --> 00:09:17,760
Please enjoy yourselves.

65
00:09:18,360 --> 00:09:19,480
Good evening, Mr. Rakchart.

66
00:09:20,120 --> 00:09:22,240
Let's go inside.

67
00:09:23,440 --> 00:09:24,440
I'll head over there.

68
00:09:25,320 --> 00:09:26,480
Please come inside.

69
00:09:44,560 --> 00:09:47,400
I'm really happy you came
to my birthday party.

70
00:09:50,320 --> 00:09:54,360
Now you understand
why I didn't want you near Dharn, right?

71
00:09:57,440 --> 00:10:00,720
I know what kind of person he is.

72
00:10:02,680 --> 00:10:04,160
Everything I did

73
00:10:05,800 --> 00:10:07,040
was because I care about you.

74
00:10:09,120 --> 00:10:12,160
I didn't think he'd be
this kind of person either.

75
00:10:15,160 --> 00:10:16,760
And not just Dharn.

76
00:10:18,240 --> 00:10:20,200
Wayu isn't trustworthy either.

77
00:10:34,800 --> 00:10:36,240
Where is he?

78
00:10:38,520 --> 00:10:40,040
I told him not to come.

79
00:10:45,120 --> 00:10:46,720
That means he knows

80
00:10:47,520 --> 00:10:49,720
this party is full of people

81
00:10:49,800 --> 00:10:52,440
who know what his father did.

82
00:10:56,880 --> 00:10:58,400
And it's being livestreamed too.

83
00:11:02,800 --> 00:11:03,880
Fahsai.

84
00:11:06,680 --> 00:11:08,160
About that day,

85
00:11:10,080 --> 00:11:12,960
I know you didn't want to see him die.

86
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:17,320
I know you well.

87
00:11:19,520 --> 00:11:23,960
There's no way you'd fall
for a low-class thug like him.

88
00:11:40,960 --> 00:11:42,520
You're just going to stand there?

89
00:11:43,320 --> 00:11:47,120
Why don't you go help
the siblings reconcile?

90
00:11:48,360 --> 00:11:49,280
Go.

91
00:11:53,720 --> 00:11:55,200
Fahsai.

92
00:11:56,640 --> 00:11:58,760
I've missed you. It's been a long time.

93
00:11:58,840 --> 00:12:01,320
Are you feeling better now?

94
00:12:02,040 --> 00:12:02,960
Yes.

95
00:12:03,880 --> 00:12:06,240
Good, because Mr. Samut and I

96
00:12:06,920 --> 00:12:08,880
were really worried about you.

97
00:12:16,640 --> 00:12:17,680
Well…

98
00:12:17,760 --> 00:12:20,840
Didn't you say you'd invite her
to dinner when you met her?

99
00:12:22,520 --> 00:12:25,040
She's right here.

100
00:12:32,600 --> 00:12:33,920
I was just about to ask.

101
00:12:34,440 --> 00:12:37,320
Fahsai, now that you're better,

102
00:12:37,400 --> 00:12:38,680
we should celebrate.

103
00:12:51,080 --> 00:12:54,320
I've been busy lately.
There's a lot to prepare.

104
00:13:03,120 --> 00:13:04,560
Happy birthday.

105
00:13:24,280 --> 00:13:25,520
Thank you.

106
00:13:28,200 --> 00:13:30,600
I've kept every birthday gift

107
00:13:33,800 --> 00:13:36,440
you've ever given me, including this one.

108
00:13:50,640 --> 00:13:55,360
Real life is even more dramatic
than the dramas you act in, Maysa.

109
00:14:01,960 --> 00:14:06,840
<i>Happy birthday to you</i>

110
00:14:15,480 --> 00:14:17,160
Thank you. Thank you very much.

111
00:14:20,080 --> 00:14:22,560
Happy birthday to MP Mahasamut,

112
00:14:22,640 --> 00:14:24,600
whom the Thai people have now

113
00:14:24,680 --> 00:14:27,440
named the nation's big brother.

114
00:14:28,720 --> 00:14:29,880
Thank you very much.

115
00:14:30,440 --> 00:14:34,400
Thank you all for honoring me
by attending my birthday tonight.

116
00:14:34,920 --> 00:14:36,680
I'm very happy today.

117
00:14:42,920 --> 00:14:44,040
Really very happy.

118
00:14:47,760 --> 00:14:51,600
Not only is MP Mahasamut
extremely happy tonight,

119
00:14:51,680 --> 00:14:55,400
Minister Rakchart is just as happy.

120
00:14:55,480 --> 00:14:59,560
He also has good news
he would like to share with everyone.

121
00:15:00,400 --> 00:15:02,000
Please welcome Minister Rakchart.

122
00:15:11,000 --> 00:15:13,520
First of all, thank you all

123
00:15:14,040 --> 00:15:16,600
for coming tonight
to celebrate my son's birthday.

124
00:15:18,480 --> 00:15:22,280
Our family is very happy
and deeply touched.

125
00:15:24,000 --> 00:15:25,680
I'd like to take this opportunity

126
00:15:26,280 --> 00:15:29,240
to share another piece of good news
and invite everyone to celebrate with us.

127
00:15:34,440 --> 00:15:35,360
What news?

128
00:15:35,440 --> 00:15:38,120
Probably about Dharn
losing his place in the public eye.

129
00:15:40,040 --> 00:15:43,400
And the party's popularity
is coming back to us.

130
00:15:47,400 --> 00:15:48,240
Fahsai, my dear.

131
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:01,560
I'm sure you all know my daughter, Fahsai.

132
00:16:03,080 --> 00:16:05,400
But there's something you don't yet know.

133
00:16:06,560 --> 00:16:09,520
This is the good news of our family.

134
00:16:10,760 --> 00:16:12,360
As her father,

135
00:16:12,440 --> 00:16:17,080
I'd like to invite you to my daughter's
wedding with Mr. Wayu Buranachat,

136
00:16:17,920 --> 00:16:19,520
which will take place next month.

137
00:17:03,640 --> 00:17:07,240
Mr. Wayu is the heir
of Mr. Chaichana Buranachat,

138
00:17:07,319 --> 00:17:10,280
the prominent businessman
I'm sure you all know well.

139
00:17:11,839 --> 00:17:13,960
Today is full of good news.

140
00:17:14,040 --> 00:17:16,440
A birthday celebration,

141
00:17:16,520 --> 00:17:19,040
the party's rising support,

142
00:17:19,119 --> 00:17:21,440
and now an auspicious announcement.

143
00:17:21,520 --> 00:17:24,520
In that case, we must invite
the nation's big brother

144
00:17:24,599 --> 00:17:28,119
to congratulate his sister. Please.

145
00:17:40,680 --> 00:17:41,720
Let's go.

146
00:17:48,280 --> 00:17:49,480
Everyone's watching.

147
00:18:20,400 --> 00:18:21,400
You see that, right?

148
00:18:22,320 --> 00:18:23,880
Everyone is watching you.

149
00:18:30,200 --> 00:18:33,200
Everyone, please join us
in raising a glass

150
00:18:33,280 --> 00:18:36,560
to celebrate the future
bride and groom in advance.

151
00:18:37,240 --> 00:18:38,560
Cheers.

152
00:19:03,320 --> 00:19:04,360
MINISTER RAKCHART ANNOUNCED
HIS DAUGHTER'S SURPRISE WEDDING

153
00:19:04,440 --> 00:19:05,360
I JUST SAW THE NEWS

154
00:19:08,760 --> 00:19:12,200
His surprises never disappoint.

155
00:19:12,720 --> 00:19:15,000
Don't get so excited
you forget to spread the news.

156
00:19:15,640 --> 00:19:18,200
I'll make social media explode.

157
00:19:19,360 --> 00:19:22,080
Tricking a woman into marrying him,
what's there to cheer about?

158
00:19:24,600 --> 00:19:26,040
We're not the only side benefiting.

159
00:19:26,120 --> 00:19:29,960
Exactly. Those people are using him
to patch up their own problems too.

160
00:19:31,840 --> 00:19:33,880
I don't doubt Rakchart.

161
00:19:33,960 --> 00:19:35,760
But what about Fahsai?

162
00:19:35,840 --> 00:19:38,280
Does she even know she's being used?

163
00:19:39,680 --> 00:19:41,960
Aren't you seeing Mahasamut's sister
as too naive?

164
00:19:42,640 --> 00:19:44,840
That woman needs Wayu as a shield.

165
00:19:45,480 --> 00:19:46,760
It's a win-win for both sides.

166
00:19:47,280 --> 00:19:50,160
But this is a woman's married life.

167
00:19:50,240 --> 00:19:52,440
Just to tear off Samut's mask,

168
00:19:52,520 --> 00:19:54,440
do we really have to go this far?

169
00:19:58,800 --> 00:19:59,840
But I think

170
00:20:00,560 --> 00:20:02,200
Pud has a point.

171
00:20:02,800 --> 00:20:05,240
Wayu seems especially serious
about this case.

172
00:20:06,160 --> 00:20:07,600
Is there something going on
behind the scenes?

173
00:20:11,720 --> 00:20:13,040
What else could it be?

174
00:20:13,120 --> 00:20:15,840
He probably just sees how rotten they are.

175
00:20:15,920 --> 00:20:18,440
He has always gone
after corrupt politicians like this.

176
00:20:31,200 --> 00:20:33,840
Samut! What the hell is wrong with you?

177
00:20:37,080 --> 00:20:38,520
How could you do this to me, Dad?

178
00:20:39,960 --> 00:20:43,000
I'm willing to do anything
to make you a minister,

179
00:20:43,080 --> 00:20:44,520
even prime minister.

180
00:20:44,600 --> 00:20:48,200
But can you stop obsessing over Fahsai
and focus on your own future?

181
00:20:48,280 --> 00:20:50,120
You made the wrong move

182
00:20:50,200 --> 00:20:52,680
bringing him in
to keep me away from Fahsai.

183
00:20:53,200 --> 00:20:55,800
Don't you realize he's using you?

184
00:20:55,880 --> 00:20:58,880
Who are you talking to? Someone like me

185
00:20:59,840 --> 00:21:01,800
doesn't get used that easily.

186
00:21:02,680 --> 00:21:05,360
It has to be win-win for both sides.

187
00:21:05,880 --> 00:21:07,360
So you admit it, right?

188
00:21:08,880 --> 00:21:11,920
You're making him marry Fahsai as a cover.

189
00:21:13,400 --> 00:21:16,400
You heard her say
she loves Wayu, didn't you?

190
00:21:16,480 --> 00:21:19,360
She just didn't want to see me kill him.

191
00:21:21,520 --> 00:21:23,160
I don't believe

192
00:21:24,280 --> 00:21:26,560
Fahsai could love a gangster like him.

193
00:21:28,520 --> 00:21:31,520
I will never accept him
as my brother-in-law.

194
00:21:33,480 --> 00:21:37,920
I'll never let this wedding happen.

195
00:21:41,480 --> 00:21:44,160
If you don't believe me,
just wait and see.

196
00:21:47,680 --> 00:21:48,840
Damn it!

197
00:22:12,400 --> 00:22:15,520
Looks like Samut's
not going to give in easily.

198
00:22:21,360 --> 00:22:22,200
It's fine.

199
00:22:23,640 --> 00:22:26,200
At least we've cleared the first hurdle.

200
00:22:27,760 --> 00:22:30,400
Thank you very much for your support, sir.

201
00:22:41,000 --> 00:22:43,760
About my son hurting you,

202
00:22:46,080 --> 00:22:47,160
can you…

203
00:22:47,920 --> 00:22:51,760
not tell anyone?
Please keep it a secret. I'm asking you.

204
00:22:55,880 --> 00:22:57,280
Dad.

205
00:22:57,360 --> 00:23:00,160
Don't you think Samut
should take some responsibility?

206
00:23:00,760 --> 00:23:03,160
Of course I do. But…

207
00:23:04,280 --> 00:23:05,120
Well,

208
00:23:05,200 --> 00:23:08,400
I believe you feel guilty and truly care.

209
00:23:09,640 --> 00:23:12,120
And you've already shown me
a lot of kindness.

210
00:23:14,360 --> 00:23:16,280
I'll keep this a secret.

211
00:23:19,000 --> 00:23:19,840
Thank you.

212
00:23:21,440 --> 00:23:22,400
Thank you very much.

213
00:23:26,880 --> 00:23:28,480
But what's concerning is…

214
00:23:29,960 --> 00:23:32,520
if Mr. Samut
can't control himself like this,

215
00:23:34,280 --> 00:23:37,560
you might have to do something about it.

216
00:23:40,640 --> 00:23:44,440
I think I might
have to send Fahsai to the US,

217
00:23:48,840 --> 00:23:51,560
even though I want to keep her close.

218
00:23:58,160 --> 00:24:00,600
I think I have a better solution.

219
00:24:04,720 --> 00:24:07,960
Have you ever thought
about Ms. Fahsai getting married?

220
00:24:13,880 --> 00:24:15,560
If she gets married,

221
00:24:16,600 --> 00:24:18,920
Mr. Samut will stop interfering.

222
00:24:19,800 --> 00:24:22,920
And Ms. Fahsai will have someone
to protect and take care of her.

223
00:24:26,360 --> 00:24:29,320
You mean… marry you?

224
00:24:31,080 --> 00:24:32,000
Yes.

225
00:24:32,600 --> 00:24:33,600
No.

226
00:24:35,360 --> 00:24:36,800
I disagree.

227
00:24:37,440 --> 00:24:39,560
Dad, we should let him rest.

228
00:24:44,080 --> 00:24:45,800
You don't have to answer now.

229
00:24:47,640 --> 00:24:49,720
Think it through, pros and cons.

230
00:24:51,640 --> 00:24:52,520
You still have time.

231
00:24:58,760 --> 00:25:00,040
But not much.

232
00:25:11,360 --> 00:25:14,720
Why are you taking so long to decide?

233
00:25:16,120 --> 00:25:19,440
Mr. Wayu is such an <i>oppa</i>.

234
00:25:21,840 --> 00:25:22,960
If it were me,

235
00:25:23,040 --> 00:25:25,360
I'd say yes before he even asked.

236
00:25:25,440 --> 00:25:29,480
I'm blushing!

237
00:25:30,120 --> 00:25:32,400
I think Samut won't stop.

238
00:25:33,640 --> 00:25:37,840
If we get married,
he might target Wayu even more.

239
00:25:40,680 --> 00:25:42,240
I see.

240
00:25:42,320 --> 00:25:44,040
I understand now.

241
00:25:44,920 --> 00:25:49,840
So the reason you haven't said yes
is because you're worried about him.

242
00:25:53,320 --> 00:25:57,520
It's better if he thinks
I don't want to get married.

243
00:25:59,240 --> 00:26:02,960
Then what about the truth?
Do you want to marry him or not?

244
00:26:05,280 --> 00:26:08,920
I've never thought about marriage,

245
00:26:10,080 --> 00:26:12,440
especially not in a situation like this.

246
00:26:16,400 --> 00:26:17,560
You don't trust me?

247
00:26:20,240 --> 00:26:21,920
I told you

248
00:26:22,760 --> 00:26:25,280
I won't let your brother hurt you again.

249
00:26:31,920 --> 00:26:33,480
<i>Sangnamja.</i>

250
00:26:34,760 --> 00:26:36,360
What a real man.

251
00:26:36,440 --> 00:26:39,320
I hope your negotiation succeeds.

252
00:26:39,400 --> 00:26:40,840
I'm rooting for you.

253
00:26:46,200 --> 00:26:48,680
<i>Oppa</i> touched my hand.

254
00:26:49,320 --> 00:26:52,040
I'm going to the restroom.

255
00:27:04,800 --> 00:27:06,960
I don't want you
risking yourself for this.

256
00:27:07,760 --> 00:27:10,600
You should just quit.

257
00:27:18,360 --> 00:27:19,920
If you're worried about me,

258
00:27:21,920 --> 00:27:23,400
then protect me.

259
00:27:27,440 --> 00:27:29,640
That day, your brother didn't shoot me

260
00:27:30,800 --> 00:27:32,400
because he was afraid of you.

261
00:27:42,640 --> 00:27:45,360
I don't know if he'll listen to me again.

262
00:27:47,920 --> 00:27:49,280
If I quit,

263
00:27:49,880 --> 00:27:53,040
I'll be an easy target.

264
00:27:54,840 --> 00:27:56,360
If you don't want me dead,

265
00:27:57,040 --> 00:27:59,880
then let me become part of your family.

266
00:28:04,720 --> 00:28:05,960
But we don't love each other.

267
00:28:11,320 --> 00:28:12,880
Why get married?

268
00:28:13,920 --> 00:28:15,720
So we can both survive.

269
00:28:17,960 --> 00:28:20,360
Once Mr. Samut marries Ms. Maysa,

270
00:28:22,160 --> 00:28:23,720
things should calm down.

271
00:28:28,360 --> 00:28:31,840
After that, if you want
to cancel the agreement,

272
00:28:32,560 --> 00:28:34,880
a divorce, I'll agree.

273
00:29:01,280 --> 00:29:03,200
We agreed to work together.

274
00:29:04,680 --> 00:29:06,120
We have to go all the way.

275
00:29:07,520 --> 00:29:09,880
I know. No need to repeat it.

276
00:29:10,920 --> 00:29:13,280
So it is what it is.

277
00:29:14,240 --> 00:29:15,880
It's a mutual benefit.

278
00:29:18,760 --> 00:29:22,280
You protect me, I keep you alive.

279
00:29:27,920 --> 00:29:28,880
Good.

280
00:29:29,480 --> 00:29:30,760
Then…

281
00:29:40,120 --> 00:29:42,960
Practice, so it looks natural
on the wedding day.

282
00:29:44,360 --> 00:29:45,320
Come on.

283
00:29:57,160 --> 00:29:58,640
Here!

284
00:29:59,280 --> 00:30:00,320
Natural enough?

285
00:30:02,800 --> 00:30:04,760
Go home.

286
00:30:05,600 --> 00:30:07,080
It's about to rain.

287
00:30:10,720 --> 00:30:12,160
Are you worried I'll get sick?

288
00:30:17,520 --> 00:30:21,560
Who would want their groom
to get sick before the wedding?

289
00:30:25,480 --> 00:30:28,200
That's so nice to hear.

290
00:31:23,360 --> 00:31:25,360
I'll be fine.

291
00:31:27,240 --> 00:31:29,120
And no matter what happens,

292
00:31:32,080 --> 00:31:34,440
I'll always be right here,
holding your hand.

293
00:31:37,360 --> 00:31:38,440
I promise.

294
00:32:12,200 --> 00:32:13,240
Prapai.

295
00:32:17,240 --> 00:32:18,400
Prapai.

296
00:32:19,240 --> 00:32:20,760
Why are you standing
in the rain? Go inside.

297
00:32:24,040 --> 00:32:25,760
I came to ask you.

298
00:32:27,480 --> 00:32:29,600
Are you really going to marry Fahsai?

299
00:32:34,800 --> 00:32:35,720
Yes.

300
00:32:38,960 --> 00:32:41,440
Let's talk inside. You'll get sick.

301
00:32:42,440 --> 00:32:44,360
Samut beat you up like that,

302
00:32:45,320 --> 00:32:47,400
and you still dare marry his sister?

303
00:32:48,880 --> 00:32:52,520
Does he have to kill you
before you understand what that means?

304
00:32:55,520 --> 00:32:57,960
Why do you have
to risk yourself like this?

305
00:33:01,440 --> 00:33:02,280
I know

306
00:33:03,120 --> 00:33:06,520
you're worried about me.
But everything is part of my plan.

307
00:33:07,400 --> 00:33:08,440
I have to get back at them.

308
00:33:08,520 --> 00:33:11,200
Then why this way?

309
00:33:11,280 --> 00:33:13,600
Why do you have to marry her?

310
00:33:14,200 --> 00:33:16,040
Don't you hate them?

311
00:33:17,560 --> 00:33:18,720
I've never forgotten

312
00:33:19,480 --> 00:33:21,520
what Mahasamut did to me.

313
00:33:24,240 --> 00:33:26,400
I have to hurt him as much as possible.

314
00:33:28,440 --> 00:33:30,000
The more he loves Fahsai,

315
00:33:30,960 --> 00:33:33,440
the more I'll make him suffer
through Fahsai.

316
00:33:35,280 --> 00:33:36,600
Are you sure?

317
00:33:38,120 --> 00:33:40,680
Are you sure that you're doing
all this for revenge?

318
00:33:44,680 --> 00:33:47,000
That you're not doing this
to protect that woman?

319
00:33:55,600 --> 00:33:59,160
The only woman I'll protect

320
00:34:00,280 --> 00:34:01,280
is you.

321
00:34:10,040 --> 00:34:11,560
If you love me,

322
00:34:13,360 --> 00:34:15,320
if you want to protect me,

323
00:34:18,320 --> 00:34:19,960
can I ask you something?

324
00:34:21,679 --> 00:34:23,320
Leave them.

325
00:34:24,120 --> 00:34:25,080
Please.

326
00:34:26,760 --> 00:34:28,080
Let's go somewhere far away

327
00:34:29,400 --> 00:34:31,280
and start a simple life together.

328
00:34:37,440 --> 00:34:38,560
Please, Wayu.

329
00:34:39,600 --> 00:34:41,040
I'm begging you.

330
00:34:53,080 --> 00:34:54,719
You promised Dad

331
00:34:55,840 --> 00:34:57,360
that you'd take care of me.

332
00:34:58,840 --> 00:35:01,280
You'd do anything for me.

333
00:35:12,840 --> 00:35:13,720
Fine.

334
00:35:14,920 --> 00:35:15,920
I will.

335
00:35:18,400 --> 00:35:19,920
I'll give everything up.

336
00:35:24,080 --> 00:35:25,240
I'll give up revenge.

337
00:35:35,720 --> 00:35:37,720
Then the two of us will go somewhere,

338
00:35:39,320 --> 00:35:41,400
somewhere far away from those bastards.

339
00:36:10,640 --> 00:36:12,200
I can't do it.

340
00:36:15,680 --> 00:36:17,160
I know

341
00:36:19,120 --> 00:36:21,320
how much this has hurt you.

342
00:36:23,280 --> 00:36:26,360
You've been willing to do everything
to get revenge on them.

343
00:36:30,400 --> 00:36:32,160
What I feel

344
00:36:33,520 --> 00:36:35,560
can't compare to the loss of your mother

345
00:36:35,640 --> 00:36:37,440
and your sister.

346
00:36:43,840 --> 00:36:45,640
I can't be selfish

347
00:36:47,640 --> 00:36:50,760
and think only
about my own feelings. I can't.

348
00:36:51,920 --> 00:36:53,840
I can't…

349
00:37:22,880 --> 00:37:23,960
Mr. Wayu.

350
00:37:24,760 --> 00:37:27,320
Why didn't you tell me
you were going to marry Fahsai?

351
00:37:27,920 --> 00:37:30,920
What's really going on?
Do you love Fahsai?

352
00:37:35,080 --> 00:37:36,160
What about you?

353
00:37:37,320 --> 00:37:39,160
Do you love Mr. Samut?

354
00:37:41,560 --> 00:37:43,920
You still insist on marrying him,

355
00:37:44,000 --> 00:37:45,720
even though you don't love him.

356
00:37:48,800 --> 00:37:50,240
I'm the same.

357
00:37:54,680 --> 00:37:56,080
But you should have told me first.

358
00:37:58,000 --> 00:37:59,720
It was Minister Rakchart's order.

359
00:38:00,480 --> 00:38:03,400
What could I do? I feel suffocated too.

360
00:38:09,360 --> 00:38:11,640
I may turn off my phone
and stop answering calls for a while.

361
00:38:13,280 --> 00:38:14,880
I don't want to be
any more stressed than this.

362
00:38:21,280 --> 00:38:22,520
You still love me, don't you?

363
00:38:28,480 --> 00:38:30,160
My feelings for you

364
00:38:31,640 --> 00:38:32,920
are still the same,

365
00:38:34,400 --> 00:38:35,800
and they will never change.

366
00:38:37,440 --> 00:38:38,360
Wayu.

367
00:38:39,880 --> 00:38:42,240
- Ms. Maysa, hello.
- Hello.

368
00:38:42,320 --> 00:38:45,280
There's no filming here today, right?

369
00:38:47,200 --> 00:38:51,280
Right. I left something behind
from the previous shoot,

370
00:38:51,360 --> 00:38:52,720
so I stopped by to get it.

371
00:38:52,800 --> 00:38:54,320
You got it already, right?

372
00:38:57,720 --> 00:38:59,120
Let's go, Wayu.

373
00:39:00,520 --> 00:39:03,480
Excuse us. We have an appointment.

374
00:39:04,000 --> 00:39:06,640
Please make yourself comfortable.
I'll call a maid for you.

375
00:39:07,240 --> 00:39:08,840
- Alright.
- Let's go.

376
00:39:30,040 --> 00:39:31,160
Thank you for taking me here.

377
00:39:32,960 --> 00:39:35,120
When you want to go back,
call Praya to pick you up.

378
00:39:36,800 --> 00:39:38,160
Wait.

379
00:39:40,720 --> 00:39:43,040
You still didn't answer me last night.

380
00:39:46,000 --> 00:39:47,040
Let's talk inside.

381
00:39:56,600 --> 00:39:58,240
If you succeed in your revenge,

382
00:40:00,840 --> 00:40:03,560
will you go back to being the old Peeraka

383
00:40:05,120 --> 00:40:07,840
and see me as a woman?

384
00:40:11,000 --> 00:40:12,360
A woman you can love…

385
00:40:16,720 --> 00:40:18,400
and marry?

386
00:40:23,440 --> 00:40:26,440
You are the woman I love most.

387
00:40:30,520 --> 00:40:31,920
But we're family.

388
00:40:34,000 --> 00:40:36,760
Being siblings is the best thing for us.

389
00:40:40,760 --> 00:40:41,800
Right?

390
00:40:50,680 --> 00:40:52,520
When that day comes,
maybe you'll change your mind.

391
00:41:02,080 --> 00:41:03,520
And I'll ask you again.

392
00:41:08,120 --> 00:41:09,120
Alright.

393
00:41:30,160 --> 00:41:31,600
Hey. What's wrong?

394
00:41:32,320 --> 00:41:33,760
Don't you go cycling?

395
00:41:48,480 --> 00:41:51,720
I've heard of mother-in-law problems.

396
00:41:52,320 --> 00:41:55,040
But a sister not liking her sister-in-law?
That exists too?

397
00:41:56,080 --> 00:41:58,040
I don't dislike Fahsai.

398
00:41:58,640 --> 00:42:01,520
Then why are you upset
that your brother's marrying her?

399
00:42:04,000 --> 00:42:06,040
You know what those politicians are like.

400
00:42:06,640 --> 00:42:09,480
I just don't want Wayu
getting mixed up with people like them.

401
00:42:11,280 --> 00:42:12,800
Are you worried about him
or possessive of him?

402
00:42:13,920 --> 00:42:15,080
Hey!

403
00:42:17,720 --> 00:42:20,600
What's wrong? Did I hit a nerve?

404
00:42:20,680 --> 00:42:24,040
Why can't I worry about him
or be possessive of him?

405
00:42:24,120 --> 00:42:26,360
Wayu is the best man in my life.

406
00:42:28,000 --> 00:42:30,920
You don't have anyone you love most,
so you wouldn't understand.

407
00:42:45,360 --> 00:42:46,400
This is Kul.

408
00:42:46,480 --> 00:42:47,920
MS. PEEKUL

409
00:42:48,000 --> 00:42:49,760
The woman I loved most.

410
00:42:56,600 --> 00:43:00,720
She passed away
just a few days before our wedding.

411
00:43:03,520 --> 00:43:06,000
You're lucky you still have your brother.

412
00:43:09,320 --> 00:43:10,880
When that person is gone,

413
00:43:14,240 --> 00:43:15,760
no matter how much you do for them…

414
00:43:15,840 --> 00:43:17,720
MS. PEEKUL

415
00:43:18,320 --> 00:43:19,760
…they'll never know.

416
00:43:22,000 --> 00:43:23,320
So,

417
00:43:24,680 --> 00:43:26,640
you should love your brother

418
00:43:27,760 --> 00:43:29,720
and be good to him as much as you can,

419
00:43:31,120 --> 00:43:32,600
while you still have the chance.

420
00:43:34,840 --> 00:43:38,240
I'm sorry for saying that to you.

421
00:43:39,800 --> 00:43:41,840
For saying you'd never loved anyone.

422
00:43:44,080 --> 00:43:45,400
It's fine. Forget it.

423
00:43:47,640 --> 00:43:50,240
I brought you here because I don't
want you to regret anything later.

424
00:43:52,320 --> 00:43:56,160
<i>He's investigating the Jaiaree family case</i>
<i>because he wants to find the culprit.</i>

425
00:43:58,600 --> 00:43:59,520
You really gave me

426
00:44:00,680 --> 00:44:02,040
strong medicine.

427
00:44:04,000 --> 00:44:07,360
At first, I didn't even think
I'd go to Wayu's wedding.

428
00:44:07,440 --> 00:44:09,800
So now you're thinking of going?

429
00:44:11,440 --> 00:44:14,440
Well, I'll try.

430
00:44:16,640 --> 00:44:19,920
But I'm not sure I can stay until the end.

431
00:44:20,520 --> 00:44:22,320
Then what if I go with you?

432
00:44:29,640 --> 00:44:32,000
MINISTER RAKCHART'S DAUGHTER TO MARRY
GREY-BUSINESS HEIR IN SURPRISE WEDDING

433
00:44:32,840 --> 00:44:34,240
Here we go.

434
00:44:35,200 --> 00:44:38,200
"Minister Rakchart's daughter

435
00:44:38,280 --> 00:44:40,920
to marry grey-business heir
in surprise wedding."

436
00:44:42,840 --> 00:44:45,560
Here's another one. "Namchat Thai Party

437
00:44:46,160 --> 00:44:48,440
joins forces with grey capital."

438
00:44:48,520 --> 00:44:51,120
There are tons of comments
digging up the boss's background.

439
00:44:54,160 --> 00:44:55,680
What do we do?

440
00:45:26,080 --> 00:45:28,520
Good afternoon, esteemed members.

441
00:45:31,520 --> 00:45:32,560
The party committee

442
00:45:33,440 --> 00:45:36,400
has appointed me as representative
to discuss today's party issue.

443
00:45:39,360 --> 00:45:43,600
Due to the announcement
of Mr. Wayu and Fahsai's wedding,

444
00:45:44,560 --> 00:45:48,840
our party has received
significant negative criticism.

445
00:45:52,160 --> 00:45:55,480
Outsiders are not viewing this
as only a family issue.

446
00:45:55,560 --> 00:45:57,840
They are seeing the Namchat Thai Party

447
00:45:57,920 --> 00:46:00,560
as joining hands
with a grey-capital group.

448
00:46:00,640 --> 00:46:04,160
I ask that you withdraw
the term "grey-capital group".

449
00:46:05,800 --> 00:46:06,720
Of course.

450
00:46:07,440 --> 00:46:10,320
But it's reasonable
for the public to question

451
00:46:10,400 --> 00:46:12,200
our party's transparency,

452
00:46:13,400 --> 00:46:15,680
especially when the election is near.

453
00:46:17,520 --> 00:46:19,320
These questions from the public

454
00:46:19,960 --> 00:46:22,000
are all about the past, aren't they?

455
00:46:22,840 --> 00:46:24,920
Mr. Wayu's father
has already passed away too.

456
00:46:26,200 --> 00:46:28,960
But several cases
are still pending in court.

457
00:46:29,680 --> 00:46:31,800
And they're all serious cases.

458
00:46:35,960 --> 00:46:37,360
Would you like to deny anything?

459
00:46:42,880 --> 00:46:44,560
Even he doesn't deny it.

460
00:46:46,320 --> 00:46:49,960
Because Mr. Wayu has inherited
that business to this day.

461
00:46:53,880 --> 00:46:55,160
Isn't that true?

462
00:46:55,240 --> 00:46:57,360
This is no small matter.

463
00:46:57,440 --> 00:47:00,480
That is why I would like to propose
that the committee

464
00:47:00,560 --> 00:47:03,560
vote on whether

465
00:47:03,640 --> 00:47:07,000
Mr. Wayu and Ms. Fahsai's wedding

466
00:47:07,080 --> 00:47:09,760
should proceed at this time.

467
00:47:10,800 --> 00:47:12,120
I object.

468
00:47:14,200 --> 00:47:17,840
This is a private matter
between Fahsai and Wayu.

469
00:47:17,920 --> 00:47:20,120
I'm afraid it can't be treated as private.

470
00:47:20,200 --> 00:47:23,120
Fahsai is in the public eye,

471
00:47:23,200 --> 00:47:24,360
and this issue

472
00:47:24,440 --> 00:47:27,480
has greatly affected the party's image.

473
00:47:34,080 --> 00:47:38,000
We're not opposing
your daughter's marriage, sir.

474
00:47:39,080 --> 00:47:42,120
We only ask that it be postponed
until after the election.

475
00:47:45,800 --> 00:47:49,240
I ask everyone to begin voting now.

476
00:48:14,920 --> 00:48:15,920
Please excuse me.

477
00:48:19,560 --> 00:48:21,600
I have something to announce to the media.

478
00:48:26,080 --> 00:48:27,160
Excuse me.

479
00:48:39,200 --> 00:48:41,320
See? Mr. Wayu

480
00:48:41,400 --> 00:48:44,120
is excellent at helping us solve problems.

481
00:48:46,760 --> 00:48:48,200
Please continue the vote.

482
00:48:51,960 --> 00:48:53,680
Excuse me.

483
00:48:53,760 --> 00:48:58,040
Mr. Wayu would like to invite everyone
to the press room next door.

484
00:48:58,120 --> 00:48:59,120
Right now.

485
00:49:00,680 --> 00:49:01,800
Press conference?

486
00:49:05,960 --> 00:49:07,280
What press conference?

487
00:49:07,800 --> 00:49:09,800
This way, please.

488
00:49:12,880 --> 00:49:14,320
Please, make yourselves comfortable.

489
00:49:15,600 --> 00:49:16,600
Please.

490
00:49:17,920 --> 00:49:18,880
Please.

491
00:49:36,560 --> 00:49:39,960
Since everyone is ready,
I'll begin the session.

492
00:49:40,800 --> 00:49:43,840
First of all,
thank you all for coming today.

493
00:49:44,400 --> 00:49:46,120
Some of you are here for business,

494
00:49:47,200 --> 00:49:51,080
while others are here
because of the current public speculation.

495
00:49:52,040 --> 00:49:54,920
I'll answer every question

496
00:49:55,000 --> 00:49:57,280
after presenting this project.

497
00:50:09,720 --> 00:50:12,400
Today, Thailand has fully entered

498
00:50:12,480 --> 00:50:14,600
an aged society.

499
00:50:14,680 --> 00:50:18,080
Over 20% of our population is elderly,

500
00:50:18,160 --> 00:50:20,400
and by 2035,

501
00:50:20,480 --> 00:50:23,080
it will rise to 30%,

502
00:50:23,160 --> 00:50:26,480
becoming a fully super-aged society.

503
00:50:28,640 --> 00:50:32,360
As you can see, aging-related businesses

504
00:50:32,440 --> 00:50:35,000
have been growing steadily,

505
00:50:35,080 --> 00:50:37,280
at 15-30% annually.

506
00:50:37,360 --> 00:50:40,240
That's why I've partnered
with CDN Hospital Group

507
00:50:40,320 --> 00:50:43,040
to develop "The Reward" project.

508
00:50:46,880 --> 00:50:49,800
Reward your life with The Reward.

509
00:50:50,440 --> 00:50:54,840
This is a condominium for seniors
in Bang Na with convenient transportation.

510
00:50:55,440 --> 00:50:59,240
It's designed according to WHO standards.

511
00:51:02,400 --> 00:51:04,480
We incorporate universal design

512
00:51:04,560 --> 00:51:07,240
for seniors,

513
00:51:07,320 --> 00:51:10,520
top-tier safety systems,

514
00:51:11,520 --> 00:51:16,640
nutritionists,
and 24-hour physical therapy support.

515
00:51:16,720 --> 00:51:18,600
We also provide medical transport

516
00:51:18,680 --> 00:51:22,400
and fast access to CDN Hospital.

517
00:51:24,640 --> 00:51:26,000
This project exists

518
00:51:26,080 --> 00:51:29,680
because we prioritize
the quality of life of the elderly.

519
00:51:30,560 --> 00:51:33,080
We believe that life after retirement

520
00:51:34,040 --> 00:51:36,080
should be the reward phase of life.

521
00:51:49,280 --> 00:51:51,720
There were allegations
about your involvement in grey businesses.

522
00:51:51,800 --> 00:51:56,120
Is this project an attempt
to shift public attention?

523
00:51:57,880 --> 00:51:59,760
The grey business is in the past.

524
00:52:00,600 --> 00:52:03,560
Since I took over,

525
00:52:05,080 --> 00:52:06,080
I guarantee

526
00:52:06,160 --> 00:52:09,880
all my businesses have been 100% legal.

527
00:52:10,720 --> 00:52:12,520
If people suspect this project

528
00:52:12,600 --> 00:52:16,000
is for money laundering,
what would you say?

529
00:52:16,600 --> 00:52:19,200
All investments are fully transparent.

530
00:52:20,440 --> 00:52:21,720
Actually,

531
00:52:21,800 --> 00:52:24,720
this project was initiated
when my father was still alive,

532
00:52:25,400 --> 00:52:28,160
but it was delayed

533
00:52:28,240 --> 00:52:30,400
due to land selection.

534
00:52:31,880 --> 00:52:33,880
Now we've secured the land.

535
00:52:49,960 --> 00:52:52,200
What about your father's businesses?

536
00:52:52,280 --> 00:52:54,680
I'm not suited for them,

537
00:52:55,480 --> 00:52:57,360
so I shut them down.

538
00:52:58,720 --> 00:53:00,320
Times have changed.

539
00:53:00,840 --> 00:53:02,680
I believe we're in an era

540
00:53:02,760 --> 00:53:06,080
where we can build businesses
by giving back to society.

541
00:53:30,480 --> 00:53:32,280
I didn't expect Wayu

542
00:53:32,360 --> 00:53:35,360
to use the Bang Na land for this.

543
00:53:37,400 --> 00:53:41,080
I thought he'd turn it into a casino
like we campaigned.

544
00:53:44,440 --> 00:53:47,920
Then there's nothing
to worry about now, sir.

545
00:53:50,480 --> 00:53:52,800
Mr. Wayu has great potential.

546
00:53:53,600 --> 00:53:56,000
You have a sharp eye, sir.

547
00:53:57,720 --> 00:54:01,600
- Yeah.
- So we don't have to vote now, right?

548
00:54:02,440 --> 00:54:04,760
From what I heard, I think

549
00:54:05,440 --> 00:54:06,800
there's no need.

550
00:54:07,360 --> 00:54:08,320
Everything's all set.

551
00:54:14,560 --> 00:54:16,080
Why didn't you tell me?

552
00:54:17,120 --> 00:54:18,880
When Samut attacked you earlier,

553
00:54:18,960 --> 00:54:21,240
do you know how worried I was?

554
00:54:24,440 --> 00:54:26,160
You always surprise me.

555
00:54:31,080 --> 00:54:32,080
Well,

556
00:54:32,680 --> 00:54:34,680
I wanted attention.

557
00:54:36,320 --> 00:54:38,160
Wanted to see how someone
who cares would react.

558
00:54:47,920 --> 00:54:49,160
What you've done

559
00:54:50,280 --> 00:54:53,200
didn't happen overnight.

560
00:54:56,800 --> 00:54:59,800
No one can create a project like this

561
00:55:00,720 --> 00:55:02,240
in a few days.

562
00:55:03,160 --> 00:55:04,800
You said you're a mafia.

563
00:55:06,800 --> 00:55:09,880
What kind of mafia does this?

564
00:55:13,680 --> 00:55:15,080
A stubborn one.

565
00:55:25,160 --> 00:55:27,320
I never liked my father's business.

566
00:55:29,280 --> 00:55:30,800
So I fought.

567
00:55:33,000 --> 00:55:34,600
I fought all the way.

568
00:55:36,840 --> 00:55:40,000
Your pay. Can't they just pay nicely?

569
00:55:40,080 --> 00:55:42,840
Someone has to get hurt first.

570
00:55:46,720 --> 00:55:48,120
Does your business

571
00:55:48,200 --> 00:55:51,200
ever involve deals without betrayal?

572
00:55:52,000 --> 00:55:53,920
All I see is stabbing
and shooting every day.

573
00:55:55,240 --> 00:55:56,800
What do you want me to do?

574
00:55:56,880 --> 00:55:59,520
I've been in this business for decades.

575
00:56:00,240 --> 00:56:03,600
I've got hundreds of men to take care of,
and their families too.

576
00:56:03,680 --> 00:56:05,360
You want me to sell coconut pancakes

577
00:56:05,440 --> 00:56:08,320
or noodles to feed them?

578
00:56:08,400 --> 00:56:10,920
There are hundreds of jobs

579
00:56:11,000 --> 00:56:12,880
that don't require
risking lives like this.

580
00:56:14,080 --> 00:56:16,080
And do they pay enough?

581
00:56:16,760 --> 00:56:19,120
It's better than throwing money
at people just to get them killed.

582
00:56:20,200 --> 00:56:21,960
Have you ever asked your men

583
00:56:23,000 --> 00:56:26,280
what they'd choose between money
and living longer with their families?

584
00:56:29,520 --> 00:56:33,320
Never. Why?
Because you never took the risk.

585
00:56:35,920 --> 00:56:37,320
Hey.

586
00:56:37,400 --> 00:56:39,360
My business is doing just fine.

587
00:56:40,160 --> 00:56:42,480
Why should I take risks?

588
00:56:43,440 --> 00:56:46,560
Do something that actually
benefits society. A hospital, maybe.

589
00:56:49,920 --> 00:56:51,280
Because you're a doctor,

590
00:56:51,960 --> 00:56:53,800
you want everyone here

591
00:56:53,880 --> 00:56:56,400
to become one too?

592
00:56:58,280 --> 00:57:00,840
I run a gambling den,

593
00:57:00,920 --> 00:57:03,480
and you want me
to build a hospital? Ridiculous.

594
00:57:05,280 --> 00:57:07,840
What do you think, Doctor Praya?

595
00:57:13,440 --> 00:57:16,280
If you can stand there
and watch your men get hurt and die,

596
00:57:17,200 --> 00:57:21,440
then fine. This world
doesn't fight face-to-face.

597
00:57:21,520 --> 00:57:22,960
It's all backstabbing.

598
00:57:25,800 --> 00:57:27,600
Today, your right-hand man got stabbed.

599
00:57:28,200 --> 00:57:30,480
Next time, it might be you.

600
00:57:39,560 --> 00:57:43,880
A gambling den and a hospital?
Do those even go together?

601
00:57:47,160 --> 00:57:48,800
But you did it.

602
00:57:53,200 --> 00:57:54,880
But before that,

603
00:57:55,440 --> 00:57:57,600
it took a lot of fighting with my dad.

604
00:57:58,880 --> 00:58:00,160
In the end, he gave in,

605
00:58:01,720 --> 00:58:02,800
but…

606
00:58:08,240 --> 00:58:09,480
he got shot and killed.

607
00:58:14,800 --> 00:58:16,200
I'm sorry.

608
00:58:18,240 --> 00:58:20,480
But you've restored his reputation.

609
00:58:21,880 --> 00:58:25,400
At least people see his descendants
in a better light now.

610
00:58:30,120 --> 00:58:32,040
If that includes his grandkids,

611
00:58:35,080 --> 00:58:38,160
you and I will have to work together.

612
00:58:39,720 --> 00:58:40,720
Hey.

613
00:58:41,320 --> 00:58:43,160
Let go. Hey.

614
00:58:49,520 --> 00:58:53,080
Then take me to meet your family

615
00:58:53,640 --> 00:58:55,160
and get to know them properly.

616
00:58:58,520 --> 00:59:00,080
But you've already met Prapai.

617
00:59:01,440 --> 00:59:04,320
A few words don't count.

618
00:59:08,240 --> 00:59:11,920
Alright. Then this Friday,
dinner at my place?

619
00:59:13,320 --> 00:59:16,360
No. Let's go to your spicy
salad restaurant instead.

620
00:59:17,040 --> 00:59:21,600
I'm hooked on
your "Spicy Salmon Explosion" now.

621
00:59:25,440 --> 00:59:27,040
But it's chaotic there.

622
00:59:28,520 --> 00:59:30,200
And you can't handle spicy food.

623
00:59:31,000 --> 00:59:32,200
Let's go somewhere else.

624
00:59:36,600 --> 00:59:38,200
Sounds like you don't
want me to go there.

625
00:59:40,040 --> 00:59:42,960
No, it's not that. I just don't want you
to feel uncomfortable.

626
00:59:47,400 --> 00:59:48,760
What are you hiding?

627
00:59:53,400 --> 00:59:54,360
I warned you.

628
00:59:55,640 --> 00:59:57,040
If it's too spicy,

629
00:59:57,760 --> 00:59:59,120
don't say I didn't warn you.

630
01:00:02,120 --> 01:00:03,160
I can handle it.

631
01:00:17,960 --> 01:00:19,440
Cheers.

632
01:00:25,680 --> 01:00:26,840
Who do you give it to?

633
01:00:42,560 --> 01:00:45,640
"There's a secret about MP Mahasamut
that's about to be exposed."

634
01:00:46,200 --> 01:00:47,800
Tomorrow at 11 p.m.,

635
01:00:48,320 --> 01:00:50,960
a female celebrity will be lured
into providing services there.

636
01:00:51,040 --> 01:00:52,960
My heart is with you.

637
01:00:58,200 --> 01:01:00,960
I now give my beloved daughter

638
01:01:01,040 --> 01:01:01,920
to the groom.

639
01:01:02,760 --> 01:01:05,160
Kiss! Kiss! Kiss!

640
01:01:08,040 --> 01:01:10,960
‪SPECIAL THANKS

641
01:02:02,360 --> 01:02:05,000
Subtitle translation by:
Panuwat Baikeawon
